---
import Container from "@/components/Container.astro";
import SectionTitle from "@/components/SectionTitle.astro";
import FramedImage from "@/components/FramedImage.astro";
import ScheduleItem from "@/components/ScheduleItem.astro";
import whoConversation from "@/assets/who-conversation.jpg";
---

<div id="format">
  <Container class="max-w-4xl">
    <SectionTitle>Format</SectionTitle>
  </Container>

  <Container class="max-w-4xl pt-14">
    <h3 class="mb-4">What to expect</h3>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="mb-4">
        This is a <span class="font-semibold">
          no-audience, full participation event</span
        >, so come ready to engage and have fun. No prior improv experience is
        necessary, just a willingness to play and laugh.
      </p>
      <p>
        Expect lots of laughter, eye rolls, and groans, and maybe even a blush
        or ten. Bring your best (or worst) cheesy pick-up lines, an open mind,
        and a sense of humor. By the end, you'll feel more confident letting
        your genuine flirty self shine through everywhere you go.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>

  <Container
    class="grid max-w-4xl items-center gap-10 pt-16 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-14"
  >
    <FramedImage
      src={whoConversation}
      alt="Two people flirting in conversation"
      imgClass="h-80"
      class="order-last md:order-first"
    />
    <div>
      <h3 class="mb-4">Who should come?</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This event is for adults of all flirting experience levels, relationship
        types, preferences, and curiosities. Statistically the host and most
        attendees tend to be straight women and men, and we aim for male/female
        gender balance to create natural flirting dynamics, but everyone is
        genuinely welcome.
      </p>
      <p class="font-display text-xl text-accent italic">
        No previous improv (or flirting) experience is required.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>

  <Container class="max-w-3xl pt-16">
    <div class="mb-3 flex flex-wrap items-end justify-between gap-2">
      <h3>Fun &amp; Games</h3>
      <span class="font-display text-lg text-accent italic"
        >about 2 hours together</span
      >
    </div>
    <p class="mb-8">
      Every Flirt Improv event has different themes and games, but there's a
      common structure:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <ScheduleItem minutes="20" title="Warm-up Games">
        Light-hearted connection games to get everyone comfortable and in the
        mood for fun.
      </ScheduleItem>
      <ScheduleItem minutes="40" title="Flirting Scenarios">
        In groups or pairs, we act out different flirting scenarios, from
        everyday situations to real stories from our lives. Expect to play
        characters and get creative with your approach.
      </ScheduleItem>
      <ScheduleItem minutes="20" title="Pick-Up Lines">
        Share and rate cheesy pick-up lines, learning to appreciate the humor
        while practicing our delivery.
      </ScheduleItem>
      <ScheduleItem minutes="25" title="Storytelling">
        Participants share personal anecdotes related to flirting: successes,
        failures, or just plain funny. A great way to connect, learn from each
        other, and maybe have a corrective emotional experience.
      </ScheduleItem>
      <ScheduleItem minutes="15" title="Reflection">
        We wrap up with a group discussion about what we learned, how we felt,
        and how to apply these skills in real life.
      </ScheduleItem>
    </ol>
  </Container>
</div>
